persName.note:
(c.1727–1783) Possibly hack writer and biographer, aka Nathaniel
                            Spencer, who produced travel accounts of Scotland among other places;
                            was not really a doctor.

Lawrence Dundas, (1712-1781) floated as patron of Low's Tour, owned
                            most of the Northern Isles; general oligarch and unsavoury character;
                            war and slavery profiteer; nicknamed the 'Nabob of the North'
